This is a custom overlay of the Nomad pot task driver with one change:

- Adds `-S dual` to `pot prepare` arguments, enabling IPv6 dual-stack
  networking in pot jails. This is required for actix-web applications
  (like AppFlowy Cloud) that create PF_INET6 sockets for HTTP servers.

Without this patch, FreeBSD jails created by the pot driver have IPv6
disabled (`ip6=disable`), which causes `EPROTONOSUPPORT` (Protocol not
supported) errors when actix-web attempts to bind to `[::]:PORT`.

The patch is a one-line addition to driver/prepare.go:

    argv = append(argv, "prepare", ..., "-S", "dual")
